Pure Function Javascipt:
pure fn is a function that given the same input will 
always return the same output and has no side effect .
It doesn't depend on external variables or modify any external state.

// Pure function
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}

// Example usage
const result = add(3, 5); // Output: 8

Impure Functions:

An impure function is a function that may have side effects or produce different results for the same input.
Side effects can include modifying external variables, changing the state of an object, or performing I/O operations.

Example of an impure function:
// Impure function
let total = 0;

function addToTotal(value) {
  total += value;
  console.log(`Total is now: ${total}`);
}

// Example usage
addToTotal(5); // Output: Total is now: 5
